      },
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#iriMinting"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#rdfTransformation"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#entityResolution"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#provenance"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#semanticEnrichment"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/abstract": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Extends the standard Bronze/Silver/Gold medallion data architecture by transforming the Gold layer into a semantic knowledge graph — enabling entity resolution, cross-system queries, impact analysis, and unified metadata via DCAT and PROV-O standards."
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/articleBody": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "The article introduces the Semantic Medallion architecture that transforms traditional data lakehouse layers into a connected knowledge graph. The Bronze layer handles raw ingestion. The Silver layer cleans data and mints stable IRIs for every entity. The Gold layer maps DataFrames to a shared ontology using OTTR templates and the maplib library, then publishes as RDF. DCAT vocabulary provides standardized catalog metadata, while PROV-O enables queryable data lineage. The result is a data catalog that answers relational questions like 'Show me everything about this record' and 'Which sources contribute to our customer records?' rather than serving static table lists."
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/author": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#veronikaHeimsbakk"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/dateModified": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date",
        "@value": "2026-05-18"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/datePublished": [
      {
